[Patient] How much water should I drink each day to manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for 8-10 cups of water daily to help your heart function well. 
[Patient] I can't afford to buy bottled water, what should I do?
[Educator] Try using a water filter or look for community resources for free water options. 
[Patient] Is it okay to drink fruit juices instead of water?
[Educator] Fruit juices may have high sugar content, stick to water or low-sodium options. 
[Patient] I live in an unsafe area, how can I ensure my water is clean?
[Educator] Consider using a water filtration system or reaching out to local resources for help. 
[Patient] Can I drink sports drinks instead of water for hydration?
[Educator] Sports drinks may have excess sugar and sodium, opt for plain water or low-sugar options.